# Shift Tracker Application - Feature Specifications

## Overview
This document outlines the detailed feature specifications for the Shift Tracker web application. Each feature includes user flows, data requirements, and integration points with the existing database schema.

## 2. Favorite Shifts

### 2.1 Create Favorite Shifts
**Description:** Allows users to create shift templates with all required fields.
**User Flow:**
1. User navigates to Favorites Management page
2. User clicks "Add New Favorite Shift" button
3. System displays form with:
   - Title (required)
   - Start Time (required, time format HH:mm)
   - End Time (required, time format HH:mm)
   - Pay Rate (required, decimal value)
   - Client (optional)
   - Color (required, 6 different Pastal color Options)
4. User fills in all required fields
5. System validates data according to schema rules
6. System creates record in FavoriteShifts collection
7. System displays success message and refreshes favorites list

**Data Requirements:**
- Title (string, required)
- Start Time (time object, required)
- End Time (time object, required)
- Pay Rate (number, positive value, required)
- Client (string, optional)
- Color (hex color code, required)

**Integration Points:**
- Database: FavoriteShifts collection
- Validation: Schema validation rules

### 2.2 View Favorite Shifts
**Description:** Displays all favorite shifts.
**User Flow:**
1. User navigates to Favorites Management page
2. System retrieves all records from FavoriteShifts collection
3. System displays list of favorite shifts with:
   - Title
   - Start Time
   - End Time
   - Pay Rate
   - Client
   - Color indicator
4. Each shift is displayed in a visually distinct panel

**Data Requirements:**
- All fields from FavoriteShifts collection

**Integration Points:**
- Database: FavoriteShifts collection
- UI: Bento-style panels for each favorite shift

### 2.3 Edit Favorite Shifts
**Description:** Allows users to modify existing favorite shift templates.
**User Flow:**
1. User navigates to Favorites Management page
2. User clicks "Edit" button on desired favorite shift
3. System displays pre-filled form with current values
4. User modifies fields as needed
5. System validates data according to schema rules
6. System updates record in FavoriteShifts collection
7. System displays success message and refreshes favorites list

**Data Requirements:**
- All fields from FavoriteShifts collection (with updated values)

**Integration Points:**
- Database: FavoriteShifts collection with update operation
- Validation: Schema validation rules

### 2.4 Delete Favorite Shifts
**Description:** Allows users to remove favorite shift templates.
**User Flow:**
1. User navigates to Favorites Management page
2. User clicks "Delete" button on desired favorite shift
3. System displays confirmation dialog
4. If confirmed, system deletes record from FavoriteShifts collection
5. System displays success message and refreshes favorites list

**Data Requirements:**
- FavoriteShift ID (to identify which record to delete)

**Integration Points:**
- Database: FavoriteShifts collection with delete operation

## 3. Shift Management

### 3.1 Add Shifts from Favorites
**Description:** Allows users to quickly add favorite shift templates to any day in calendar views.
**User Flow:**
1. User navigates to Week or Month view page
2. User clicks on desired date
3. System displays modal with user's favorite shifts
4. User selects a favorite shift template
5. System creates new Shift record in Shifts collection:
   - Sets date to selected day
   - Sets favoriteShiftId to selected favorite shift ID
   - Copies other fields (title, startTime, endTime, payRate, client, color) from favorite shift
6. System displays success message and refreshes calendar view

**Data Requirements:**
- Date (from calendar selection)
- FavoriteShift ID (to reference template)
- All fields copied from FavoriteShifts collection

**Integration Points:**
- Database: Shifts collection
- Relationships: userId to Users collection, favoriteShiftId to FavoriteShifts collection
- Calendar views: WeekView and MonthView components

### 3.2 Edit Shifts
**Description:** Allows users to modify existing shift records.
**User Flow:**
1. User navigates to Week or Month view page
2. User clicks on existing shift in calendar view
3. System displays edit form with current shift details
4. User modifies fields as needed
5. System validates data according to schema rules
6. System updates record in Shifts collection
7. System displays success message and refreshes calendar view

**Data Requirements:**
- All fields from Shifts collection (with updated values)

**Integration Points:**
- Database: Shifts collection with update operation
- Validation: Schema validation rules

### 3.3 Delete Shifts
**Description:** Allows users to remove shift records.
**User Flow:**
1. User navigates to Week or Month view page
2. User clicks on existing shift in calendar view
3. System displays edit form with current shift details
4. User clicks "Delete" button
5. System displays confirmation dialog
6. If confirmed, system deletes record from Shifts collection
7. System displays success message and refreshes calendar view

**Data Requirements:**
- Shift ID (to identify which record to delete)

**Integration Points:**
- Database: Shifts collection with delete operation

### 3.4 Sort Shifts by Start Time
**Description:** Displays shifts sorted by start time within each day.
**User Flow:**
1. System retrieves shift records for a given date range
2. System sorts records by startTime field in ascending order
3. System displays shifts in calendar view in sorted order

**Data Requirements:**
- Shift records with startTime field

**Integration Points:**
- Database: Shifts collection with date and time sorting
- Calendar views: WeekView and MonthView components

## 4. Calendar Views

### 4.1 Week View
**Description:** Displays a 7-day layout showing shift summaries for each day.
**User Flow:**
1. User navigates to Week View page
2. System calculates current week based on today's date
3. System retrieves all shifts from the shift collection for the 7-day period
4. System displays 7-day layout with:
   - Day headers (date and day of week)
   - Shift summaries for each day
   - Clickable days to add favorite shifts
5. Each shift summary shows:
   - Title
   - Client
   - Color indicator

**Data Requirements:**
- Date range (7 consecutive days)
- Shift records for the date range

**Integration Points:**
- Database: Shifts collection with date range query
- UI: Bento-style panels for each shift summary
- Navigation: Previous/next week buttons

### 4.2 Month View
**Description:** Displays full calendar month with daily shift indicators.
**User Flow:**
1. User navigates to Month View page
2. System calculates current month based on today's date
3. System retrieves all shifts from Users collection for the month
4. System displays calendar grid:
   - Month header with navigation controls
   - Day headers (Sunday through Saturday)
   - Calendar days with shift indicators
   - Clickable days to add favorite shifts
5. Each day shows:
   - Date number
   - Shift indicators (color-coded dots or small panels)

**Data Requirements:**
- Date range (full month)
- Shift records for the month

**Integration Points:**
- Database: Shifts collection with date range query
- UI: Calendar grid layout with shift indicators
- Navigation: Previous/next month buttons

### 4.3 Day Selection for Adding Shifts
**Description:** Allows users to add favorite shifts to any day from calendar views.
**User Flow:**
1. User clicks on a day in either Week or Month view
2. System displays modal with user's favorite shifts
3. User selects a favorite shift template
4. System creates new Shift record as described in "Add Shifts from Favorites"

**Data Requirements:**
- Selected date
- FavoriteShift ID

**Integration Points:**
- Calendar views: WeekView and MonthView components
- Favorite shifts management: UI for selecting templates

### 4.4 Shift Details View
**Description:** Allows users to view/edit shift details by clicking on a shift.
**User Flow:**
1. User clicks on a shift in calendar view
2. System displays modal with shift details:
   - Title
   - Date
   - Start Time
   - End Time
   - Pay Rate
   - Client
   - Color
3. User can edit fields or delete shift
4. Changes are saved to database as described in "Edit Shifts" and "Delete Shifts"

**Data Requirements:**
- Shift record data

**Integration Points:**
- Database: Shifts collection
- UI: Modal form for viewing/editing details

## 5. User Interface

### 5.1 Pages
**Description:** Defines all pages in the application with their purpose and navigation.
**Pages:**
1. **Favorites Management Page**
   - Purpose: Manage favorite shift templates
   - Navigation: From dashboard
2. **Week View Page**
   - Purpose: Display weekly shift schedule
   - Navigation: From dashboard
3. **Month View Page**
   - Purpose: Display monthly shift schedule
   - Navigation: From dashboard

**Data Requirements:**
- Page-specific UI components and data requirements

**Integration Points:**
- Routing system for page navigation
- Authentication middleware to protect pages

### 5.2 Bento-Style Design
**Description:** Implements modular panels with rounded corners and soft gradients.
**User Flow:**
1. All UI components are styled as bento-style panels
2. Panels have:
   - Rounded corners (8px radius)
   - Soft background gradients
   - Subtle shadows for depth
   - Consistent spacing and alignment
3. Components include:
   - Login/registration forms
   - Favorite shift cards
   - Shift summary panels
   - Calendar views

**Data Requirements:**
- CSS styling rules for bento-style components

**Integration Points:**
- Frontend framework (React/Vue/Angular)
- CSS framework or custom styling system

### 5.3 Smooth Animations
**Description:** Implements smooth transitions for form transitions and view changes.
**User Flow:**
1. Page transitions have fade-in/fade-out effects
2. Form modals slide in from bottom or center
3. Calendar navigation has smooth transitions between weeks/months
4. Shift creation/editing has smooth animations for UI updates

**Data Requirements:**
- Animation timing and easing functions

**Integration Points:**
- CSS transitions and animations
- Frontend framework animation capabilities

### 5.4 Close Buttons
**Description:** Provides close functionality for all pop-up forms and views.
**User Flow:**
1. All modals and pop-ups have visible close buttons (X icon)
2. Clicking close button dismisses the modal/view
3. Forms can be closed without saving changes

**Data Requirements:**
- UI elements with close functionality

**Integration Points:**
- Frontend component structure for modals
- Event handling for close actions

### 5.5 Mobile-Friendly Responsive Design
**Description:** Ensures application works well on all device sizes.
**User Flow:**
1. Layout adjusts based on screen size
2. Touch-friendly controls and buttons
3. Responsive grid system for calendar views
4. Appropriate font sizing and spacing for mobile

**Data Requirements:**
- Responsive CSS media queries
- Mobile-first design approach

**Integration Points:**
- CSS framework or custom responsive system
- Frontend component structure
